<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 13 at 3:45AM EST  by NWS Charleston</headline>
<description>Overnight snowfall amounting to an inch or two, even as high as
two to four inches above 3000 feet, can coat untreated surfaces
during the early morning hours.
The snow will cause decreased visibility and can cause slippery
road conditons, especially over higher terrain. Allow extra time,
slow down and allow extra space between you and the vehicle ahead
of you. Avoid sudden breaking, accelerating and turning as much as
possible.</description>
